50|$|Mathias Wenda is the Commander in Chief of the West Papua Revolutionary Army (WPRA). He {{has been}} active in West <b>Papua</b> {{independence}} <b>movement</b> since his early age in his village, Pyramid, West Papua. In 1977, became the leader of the fight against the Indonesian occupation. He fled to Papua New Guinea upon the surrender of most of the villagers in 1980.|$|R
